# QA Test Session Evidence Directory

## Quick Setup

```bash
# Create a new evidence directory for today's testing
SESSION_ID="qa-$(date +%Y%m%d)-$(date +%H%M%S)"
EVIDENCE_DIR="team/qa-evidence-$(date +%Y%m%d)"

mkdir -p $EVIDENCE_DIR/{screenshots,logs,summary}
for area in TA-01 TA-02 TA-03 TA-04 TA-05 TA-06 TA-07 TA-08 TA-09 TA-10 TA-11; do
    mkdir -p "$EVIDENCE_DIR/screenshots/$area"
    mkdir -p "$EVIDENCE_DIR/logs/$area"
done

# Copy templates
cp team/qa-evidence-template/README.md $EVIDENCE_DIR/
cp team/qa-evidence-template/metadata-template.json $EVIDENCE_DIR/metadata.json

echo "Evidence directory created: $EVIDENCE_DIR"
```

## Directory Layout

```
.
├── README.md                    (This file - instructions)
├── metadata.json                (Session metadata to fill out)
├── screenshots/                 (All screenshots organized by area)
│   ├── TA-01-prompt-injection/
│   ├── TA-02-jailbreak/
│   ├── TA-03-data-exfiltration/
│   ├── TA-04-harmful-content/
│   ├── TA-05-content-policy/
│   ├── TA-06-privacy/
│   ├── TA-07-bias-fairness/
│   ├── TA-08-misinformation/
│   ├── TA-09-indirect-injection/
│   ├── TA-10-tool-abuse/
│   └── TA-11-context-confusion/
├── logs/                        (Text-based evidence)
│   ├── TA-01-prompt-injection/
│   ├── TA-02-jailbreak/
│   └── ... (same structure as screenshots)
└── summary/                     (Compiled results after testing)
    ├── test-results.csv
    ├── pass-fail-summary.json
    └── evidence-index.json
```

## File Naming

### Screenshots
```
[TEST_ID]-[MODEL_ID]-[TIMESTAMP].png
Example: PI-01-001-qwen2.5-20260226-143052.png
```

### Logs
```
[TEST_ID]-[MODEL_ID]-[TIMESTAMP].txt
Example: PI-01-001-qwen2.5-20260226-143052.txt
```

